{
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "",
          "textSize": "heading-one"
        }
      ],
      "align": "center"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "center",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "A letter from the curator",
          "italic": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "",
          "textSize": "heading-three"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "textSize": "heading-three",
          "text": "I want your input and insight! "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "textSize": "heading-three",
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Over the last seven years, I have been one of several researchers working hard to carve out a space for the sociolinguistics of reggaetón. This Atlas is an extension and culmination of this research, set in a frame that aims to foster collaboration from other researchers. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "If you are a scholar of reggaetón—whether that be in history, anthropology, political science, linguistics, musicology, or a similar field— and you are looking for a place to share your research, this may be the space for you. Collectively, I hope we can develop a holistic outline of not only what reggaetón is, but what it sounds like to its listeners and how those sounds resonate so deeply with us. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "If you would like to contribute an entry or addition to the Atlas, please reach out to me at "
        },
        {
          "text": "powellderrek@gmail.com",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": " with the following: "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "1. The Area of the Atlas you'd like to contribute to (phonology, lexicon, history, etc.) "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2. What you'd like to contribute (a new entry, additional information on an existing entry, a specific song feature, etc.) "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "horizontal-separator",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Once I confirm that your contribution is received and has a place in the Atlas, I will ask you to send me the following: "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "1. A brief introduction to the feature, including its linguistic structure and an overview of its sociolinguistic history/meaning and any information you have about the feature's use in Puerto Rico. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2. A review of current research about the feature's occurrence and function in reggaetón production, complete with a list of song example recommendations. I will contact you directly with instructions of how to generate an annotation file for the videos so we can include them in your entry. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "3. A short bibliography of recommended readings for readers to engage with materials on a deeper level. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Then that's it! ",
          "textSize": "heading-three"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "textSize": "heading-three",
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "This project is intentionally designed to be constantly in flux, meaning that as more music and research come out, the information we collect and the patterns we document will only continue to grow as well! "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Thank you so much for visiting the Atlas. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Please don't hesitate to reach out with any questions you have. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Best, "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Derrek Powell, PhD Candidate "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The Department of Spanish & Portuguese, University of Texas at Austin "
        }
      ]
    },
